BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 1/6/1994 -- Romanian Foreign 
Minister Teodor Melescanu met on Wednesday, 1 June, with Salman 
Khursheed, state minister of the External Affairs Ministry of 
India, who is accompanying the Indian president in the visit in 
Romania. 
  The partners expressed satisfaction with the positive 
evolution of the traditional relations between Romania and 
India, as well as the belief that the dialogue at the high level 
in Bucharest would open new prospects for the bilateral 
cooperation. The two high diplomats exchanged views with regard 
to current international issues of common interest. They agreed 
to intensify the dialogue between the two foreign ministries on 
diverse issues, as well as between their representatives in 
international bodies. 

